sub_title: Economist and International Development   | Economics of Fragile and Conflict Affected states | #DataScience
summary:
Moneera Yassien is an economist and international researcher. She has over five years of work experience as a researcher and development practitioner. She is interested and focusing her work on understanding the economies of fragile and conflict affected states. 
Using mixed methods and utilising her data science skills Moneera aspires to become a leading economist in FCS.
